SENATE CHAMBER
STATE OF OKLAHOMA DISPOSITION
FLOOR AMENDMENT No. ________
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
(Date)
I move to amend House Bill No. 1807, as follows:
1. On Page 1, Line 22, by inserting a new subsection A to read as follows:
“A. The Oklahoma Water Resources Board shall require all permit holders authorized to take and
use groundwater to implement a system of measuring groundwater usage from all wells associated
with the permit. The Board shall determine which measurement systems may be utilized, which shall
include, but not be limited to, pump and irrigation monitoring telemetry devices capable of reporting
usage. Such measuring systems shall be in proper operating conditions at all times when
groundwater is being produced. Data from the measuring system shall be utilized for the annual
groundwater use report.”;
2. By renumbering subsequent subsections; and
3. On Page 3, Line 13 1/2, by inserting a new Section 2 to read as follows:
“SECTION 2. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Water Resources Board from
any monies not otherwise appropriated from the General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the
fiscal year ending June 30, 2026, the sum of Thirty Million Dollars ($30,000,000.00) or so much
thereof as may be necessary to provide funds to permit holders authorized to take and use
groundwater to implement a system of measuring groundwater usage from wells associated with the
permit.”
